result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Christine M Kaiser was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The bond previously posted shall be applied towards the fine and costs.  If probation/extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.
Defendant shall obtain and/or maintain full time employment, full time school, or a combination of the two equal to full time status.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substance without a valid prescription.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent, including an AODA assessment if agent deems necessary and shall comply with any treatment recommendations.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall obtain and maintain her residence.

timeConds.notes:
With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the
inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discrection of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.
